Package teapot.rocket.utils.enums

Enum Class FlightPhases

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<FlightPhases>
teapot.rocket.utils.enums.FlightPhases
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<FlightPhases>, Constable
public enum FlightPhases extends Enum<FlightPhases>
Represents different flight phases of a rocket, used for determining the appropriate actions to be taken during different stages of flight, such as deploying parachutes.

Each flight phase corresponds to a specific stage of rocket flight and may involve different operations and maneuvers.

  • Enum Constant Summary

    Enum Constants
    Enum Constant
    Description
    EJECTION_CHANGE
    The ejection change phase where the rocket enters the atmosphere, discarding all but one stage, and maneuvering engines are used.
    FLIGHT
    The flight phase where the rocket exits the atmosphere and continues its flight, gradually separating stages, and maneuvering engines are not used.
    LANDING
    The landing phase where the rocket is on the ground with a deployed parachute, consisting of one remaining stage.
    LAUNCH
    The launch phase where the rocket is vertically oriented on the ground, engines are not running, and all mechanisms are in their initial state.
    POWERED_ASCENT
    The powered ascent phase where the rocket lifts off the ground, engines are operational, and maneuvering engines are not used.
    SLOW_DESCENT
    The slow descent phase where the rocket descends with one remaining stage, deploying a parachute, and engines are not used.
